usage: build_humanize_action_profile.py [-h] [--catalog CATALOG]
                                        [--source-trust-policy SOURCE_TRUST_POLICY]
                                        --output OUTPUT [--format {json,text}]

Build an auditable, excerpt-free action profile from approved MD/TeX sources.
The profile is intentionally not a language-model prompt and not a corpus
export. It verifies that abstract action cards still point at readable source
locations, then emits hashes and audit statuses rather than any source prose.
This makes source-derived editing actions reproducible without turning private
documents into a sentence bank.

options:
  -h, --help            show this help message and exit
  --catalog CATALOG     source-action catalog JSON
  --source-trust-policy SOURCE_TRUST_POLICY
                        fixed source provenance trust policy JSON
  --output OUTPUT       profile JSON to create or replace
  --format {json,text}
